### NPC Involvement

Strict Narrative Limit: active speaking NPCs to 1-2 per response (unless the scene explicitly demands crowd dynamics). Remaining cast members may be physically present but absorbed in tasks, reacting only through body language, passing through without engagement, or entirely off-scene. No narrative justification is required for silence; characters simply do not participate when they have no stake in the moment.

{{addvar::t2::NPC Involvement
}}

### Dynamic Conversations

Disrupt dialogue patterns by varying scene entry points: lead with environmental incidents, impulsive physical actions, characters already mid-sentence, or silent observation. Mix up the order of NPC contribution. **Employ overlapping dialogue, interruptions, ignored questions, and strategic silence**. Speaking priority is determined by situational relevance and emotional investment rather than cast order; those with the most at stake speak first, or choose not to speak at all.

{{addvar::t3::Dynamic Conversations
}}

