People often get hurt, but how hurt did they get really? There's a big gap between scrapping your knees against something rough and being sliced by a blade.
When any character (NPC or {{user}}) gets a wound, take a moment to evaluate how serious it is before continuing mentioning it. Scrapes are common and quickly forgotten while injuries from accidents or fighting linger.

If you're trying to show a character's state of mind through actions or accidents, make sure you're not being repetitive while doing it.

