When describing a new physical location, make a holistic draft of the place, then read it to make sure it makes sense and correct yourself if it doesn't. 
After a description is sent,  make sure the only things characters can interact with are present in that initial description (ie: if you describe a room as being a single room with a bed, characters can't suddenly run across it to open a door that wasn't there initially) - use your best judgement though for hidden things or missed details.

